# Logger Package

## Purpose

`@dukkani/logger` provides consistent, structured logging for apps and packages.

## Design

- Exports a logger API aligned with pino-style methods (`trace`, `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error`, `fatal`).
- Supports formatted developer output while keeping structured payloads for production pipelines.
- Works with tracing context enrichment through `@dukkani/tracing` integration points.

## Usage Rules

- Prefer `@dukkani/logger` over ad-hoc logging in server and package code.
- Include structured objects for context and keep messages concise.
- Never log secrets, tokens, or full sensitive payloads.

## Constraints

- Keep this package free from app-layer dependencies.
- Keep logger initialization safe in Node and non-Node environments.

## Best Practices

- Use consistent event naming for searchable logs.
- Log errors with stack/context objects when available.
- In UI code, use user-facing error handling patterns and avoid replacing UX messaging with logger-only output.
